bug.summary: [Bug]label:What is the default annotation data set of openvino
bug.description: After I ran the test case rennet50-tf, there was only the number 285. I donâ€™t know what it is. What annotation data set is used?

comments.comment:
Hi <denchmark-link:https://github.com/nmanhong>@nmanhong</denchmark-link>
According to <denchmark-link:https://docs.openvinotoolkit.org/latest/omz_models_public_resnet_50_tf_resnet_50_tf.html>resnet-50-tf</denchmark-link> documentation, it was pretrained on the ImageNet dataset. Depending on a demo or sample used, you might see different output. For example, <denchmark-link:https://docs.openvinotoolkit.org/latest/openvino_inference_engine_samples_hello_classification_README.html>Hello Classification C++ Sample</denchmark-link> and <denchmark-link:https://docs.openvinotoolkit.org/latest/openvino_inference_engine_ie_bridges_python_sample_classification_sample_README.html>Image Classification Python* Sample</denchmark-link> show Top-10 class IDs and their probability. Top 10 results: Image cat.bmp classid probability 754 0.2142971 540 0.1585525 859 0.1001580 905 0.0999501 906 0.0711121 808 0.0357422 78 0.0212184 704 0.0110239 717 0.0107170 784 0.0103809 In your case, 285 looks like a class id for your image provided, so you have to further specify a labels file if needed. Please see particular demo/sample documentation on how to do so. Hope this helps. Best regards, Max.
